item.description:
Start the Daml Sandbox and JSON API Server before running any commands

1. Run `make package`;
2. Ensure the `daml.yaml` file of the 'da-marketplace doesn't have a `init-script` (ie, comment out this line);
3. Run `daml start`.
4. Make note of the da-marketplace hash generated. Take this value as set the `TemplateID` in the environment variables (ie, Select the collection "DA Marketplace 0.2.0 - Salesforce -> Variables -> TemplateId. A sample output where the hash is generated - `Generating da-marketplace-0.2.0 (hash: ed3cdcd75bbdbfdaba05d2e82b5d900f8664cf492997072f61da469af33258d5)`

The majority of commands can be ran individually. Some commands such as accepting an `Offer` require a Contract Id as input.

An Operator `Role` allows an Operator of a network to :

1. Make `Offers` to parties on the network to be providers of various services;
2. Approve `Requests` from parties who wish to provider services.

